WHO EPIDEMIOLOGICAL BULLETIN, SUMMARY FOR PERIOD 22 TO 26 JANUARY 1996
CHOLERA
BURUNDI (17 JANUARY 1996). A TOTAL OF APPROXIMATELY 2300 CHOLERA CASES HAVE
BEEN DETECTED SINCE THE END OF AUGUST 1995 IN THE PROVINCES OF BUBANZA, BURURI
AND CIBITOKE STOP RECENTLY CASES HAVE OCCURRED IN GATUMBA AND MARAMVYA RURAL
HEALTH CENTRES (BUJUMBURA RURALE PROVINCE) STOP THESE CENTRES HAVE RECEIVED
ASSISTANCE FROM MEDECINS SANS FRONTIERES (MSF), UNICEF AND WHO AND THE
EPIDEMIC APPEARS TO BE UNDER CONTROL
UP-TO-DATE INFORMATION IS NOT AVAILABLE FROM OTHER HEALTH CENTRES IN BUJUMBURA
AND OTHER PROVINCES WHERE THE CURRENT SITUATION PREVENTS VISITS BY HEALTH
TEAMS AND THE NUMBER OF CASES IS PROBABLY VASTLY UNDERESTIMATED. THE
PRECARIOUS SITUATION IN THE AREA AND THE POTENTIAL MASSIVE POPULATION
DISPLACEMENT CONTRIBUTE TO A CONTINUED THREAT OF NEW OUTBREAKS

NOTES CONCERNING THIS SERVICE:
The Weekly Epidemiological Record (WER) serves as an essential instrument
for the rapid and accurate dissemination of epidemiological information on
cases and outbreaks of diseases under the International Health Regulations,
other communicable diseases of public health importance, including the
newly emerging or re-emerging infections, non-communicable diseases and
other health problems. The WER is distributed every Friday in a bilingual
English/French edition. The electronic edition is free of charge and can
be obtained through FTP or WWW:
ftp.who.ch, user name should be "anonymous", password should be your e.mail
address. The WER issues are in the subdirectory /pub/wer
http://www.who.ch/wer/wer_home.htm
Any queries on subscription to the printed edition should be addressed
to: World Health Organization, Distribution and Sales, 20 Avenue Appia,
CH-1211 Geneva 27, Fax: (+4122) 791 48 57
Issues of the WER are in AdobeTM AcrobatTM portable document format (.pdf).
To view the WER, the programme Acrobat Reader is required
Some of the graphic images (figures) included in the printed version may
not be displayed in the file.
Separate .pdf files exist for each issue of the WER and are named according
to the volume and issue number, for example the file wer7048 contains the
WER volume 70, number 48.
To obtain help, send a message to majordomo@who.ch with the word help as
the body of the message.
